Task 1 – Digital Literacy Infographic

For this task, I used Canva to create a digital literacy awareness infographic. Canva is a 
free online design tool that allows users to create posters, infographics, and 
presentations easily using templates.
My infographic covers three important topics related to digital literacy:
1. What is Digital Literacy – It explains the ability to use digital devices, the 
internet, and online platforms effectively. 
2. Safe Internet Practices – It highlights tips such as using strong passwords, 
avoiding suspicious links, and protecting personal data online. 
3. Professional Online Presence – It explains how students should maintain 
professional profiles on platforms like LinkedIn and GitHub. 
4. Email Etiquette -It explains the importance of writing clear subject lines, using 
polite greetings, maintaining a professional tone, and ending emails with proper 
sign-offs when communicating with teachers or employers.
The infographic uses icons, colors, and short text to make the information easy to 
understand for students.
While creating this design, the most interesting part was learning how to arrange visual 
elements to make information attractive and easy to read. The main difficulty I faced 
was selecting the right layout and icons that clearly represented the concept of digital 
literacy
